markdownRunner.defaultCodes.markdownDescription:
Prepend or wrap your code blocks with default code to improve readability, by specifying for each `language (Code Block Tag)`, either the string to be prepended or the `-I@` (insert at) flag followed by whitespace and a string containing the `@` symbol where you want to insert the code. Examples:
Item: `bash`, Value: `var=123
`
Item: `cpp`, Value: `-I@ #include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
int main(){
@}
`
